5:
Well, the Diviners' Commission is
willing to provide support to your
village.
8:
However, I do have one question for
you, Maihime. What sort of future do
YOU want for your village?
11: I-I want us to coexist with yokaiâ€”
14:
That's all fine and good, but... Was
your village not attacked by yokai?
22:
There's nothing wrong with having a
more idealistic goal, but
compromising those goals with
reality is an essential part of politics.
24:
I suppose that will be your first
lesson. Once you've learned more,
you can give me your answer.
32:
Yes, if you're going to learn about
politics and yokai at the same time,
then there's no better place for you
than here.
36:
You... No, your entire village needs to
know more about the yokai. If not...
42:
On one hand, you have Orochi, an
evil yokai who spreads terror
throughout the world... But on the
other hand, the Yokai Encyclopedia
also shows yokai who wish to coexist
with humans...
45:
I didn't know about any of this... I feel
like I've barely scratched the
surface...
49:
Maihime, I made dinner. Did you
want some?
52: Yes, please come in! And thank you!
57:
Hmm... Someone's hard at work...
Everything going okay?
62:
Simply put... No. The more I learn, the
more there is TO learn.
65:
What do you think, Alk? What would
you choose to do if you were in my
position?
69: Uh... I don't think I have an answer...
76:
Come on, I'm not some genius.
There's plenty of stuff I don't know or
even understand.
79:
But I think the important part is that I
WANT to understand.
82:
Once you've decided what you want
to do, let me know. I'll help in any
way I can.
91:
Of course... The answer's been in
front of me all along! It's never
changed!
97:
Are we sure this is okay? What if the
villagers panic or something?
100:
If what Suizen said is true, we don't
have the luxury of taking things
easy... We must believe in Maihime.
103:
It seems you've made quite a few
friends... I certainly hope they
haven't been distracting you from
your studies.
106:
Of course not, Mother. And this is the
result of those studies.
109:
Maihime, what in the world are you
doing?!
111:
Don't worry. This is only temporary.
But more importantly, I want you to
meet my friends.
114:
Yokai?! Maihime, what is the
meaning of this?!
116:
Please calm down, Mother. These
yokai are good!
119:
A yokai? Good?! What nonsense!
These yokai have clearly deceived
you!
128:
No! I swear I haven't been tricked!
I'm here of my own will!
130:
Then let us ask the ancestral spirits!
They will show us the truth!
133: Why... Why did a yokai appear?!
138:
Please listen to me... Our powers as
shamans come from the yokai.
141:
According to the diviners, we've
been synchronizing with the yokai
and amplifying the power we
receive from them.
143:
And the yokai have acknowledged
our abilities and lent us their power
willingly!
146:
Then why... Why have they not said
anything?! Surely they were trying to
play us for fools!
148:
Would it not have been difficult to
convince our village of their
goodwill? We have such a traumatic
history with yokai.
151:
I know we have been hurt by yokai in
the past. And it's true that malicious
yokai still exist.
154:
But that doesn't mean all yokai are
that way. It was a yokai that helped
me as a lost little girl. And the yokai
here have been lending us power to
protect our home.
158:
Instead of only seeing the bad in
yokai... Don't you think you could try
seeing the good in them?
161:
You need not carry this burden
alone. Your daughter has grown into
a strong woman.
164:
The Diviner's Commission and the
good yokai are both working day
and night to foster a good
relationship between our two
groups.
167:
The yokai have even been doing
plays! And that's not allâ€”
170:
I... had thought the outside world
was in a much worse condition than
that.
172:
I will transfer control over part of the
village and barrier to you. You may
do with that what you wish.
173:
However... If I ever sense that the
villagers are in danger, we will return
to our previous ways. Do you
understand?
180:
The barrier's gone, but don't the
villagers and yokai seem a bit...
awkward?
183:
That's only natural, I suppose. We've
only just taken our first step towards
coexisting. But surely we'llâ€”
186:
Hey, Maihime! Where's that Yokai
Encyclopedia? I wanna know what
these yokai's names are!
189:
Here you go. By the way, this is Isha,
and the one over there is Aka
Denchu.
192:
Whoooa, have you memorized all
their names already?
194:
No, not even close. I still have much,
much more to learn about the
outside world!
